    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Removing and installing 12V battery"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Fire is strictly prohibited.",
        "The 12V battery fluid is dilute sulfuric acid and should be handled and stored with care.",
        "If 12V battery fluid gets into eyes or gets on hands or work clothes, wash immediately.",
        "Wear protective glasses when working."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "12V batteries are heavy and should be handled with care."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. 12V battery terminal disconnected",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000910",
          "label": "12V battery terminal disconnected",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "12V battery Check the precautions for cancellation and disconnect the cable from the negative (-) terminal of the 12V battery."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. 12V battery removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2224_3.0_jpn_11580697_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "12V battery Remove the setting plate (A) and remove the 12V battery (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "When the 12V battery is replaced, reset the 12V battery internal resistance value in the PGM-FI ECU."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. 12V battery Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2224_3.0_jpn_11580698_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install the 12V battery (A) and install the 12V battery setting plate (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. 12V battery terminal Connection",
